IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE LOW-INCOME HOUSING FOR DISABLED PERSONS
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE LOW-INCOME HOUSING FOR DISABLED PERSONS
IRS990.Desc: THE CORPORATION OPERATES A SEVEN UNIT LOW-INCOME APARTMENT COMPLEX IN SAN RAFAEL, CALIFORNIA FOR DEVELOPMENTALLY DISABLED ADULTS UNDER SECTION 811 OF THE NATIONAL HOUSING ACT. THE PROJECT IS REGULATED BY HUD AS TO RENT CHARGES AND OPERATING METHODS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATION HAS BEEN GRANTED TAX-EXEMPT STATUS BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE UNDER CODE SECTION 501(C)(3) AND BY THE CALIFORNIA FRANCHISE TAX BOARD UNDER CODE SECTION 23701(D). THE CORPORATION BELIEVES THAT IT DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE FEDERAL AND STATE INFORMATION RETURNS FOR THE YEARS ENDING SEPTEMBER 30, 2017, 2016, 2015 AND 2014 ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY REGULATORY AGENCIES, GENERALLY FOR THREE YEARS AND FOUR YEARS AFTER THEY WERE FILED FOR THE FEDERAL AND STATE RETURNS, RESPECTIVELY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 3: Description of Delegated Duties to Management Company
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PROJECT IS MANAGED BY EAH, INC., A NONPROFIT PUBLIC BENEFIT CORPORATION RELATED TO THE CORPORATION BY COMMON MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND/OR THE POWER TO APPOINT DIRECTORS. EAH IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE DAY TO DAY OPERATIONS OF THE LOW INCOME HOUSING PROJECT, INCLUDING MAINTENANCE OF ACCOUNTING RECORDS, RENT COLLECTION, FACILITY MAINTENANCE, ETC.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 8: Explanation of No Contemporaneously Documentation of Meetings
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THERE ARE NO SUBCOMMITTEES OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.
